column5: Set A2 was damaged beyond repair on the boat journey over from China in 2011.
Set A3 was the first A set to enter service.
Set A15 is currently home to D6342 as D6315 is being repaired after hitting a trailer in Vineyard back in 2024.
D6342 was heavily damaged when it collided with the buffer stop at Richmond back in 2019. The rest of the train partially derailed.
B2 was the first B set to enter service.
Nicknamed "Queen B" as B41 was the last B set to enter service.
In 2019, H55 was given an indigenous livery in support of the Koori Knockout. It also has "Bring the mob home safely" on one of the carriages.
J7 was the first J set to be fully refurbished back in 2014.
Ran the last revenue service through Sydenham platforms 1&2 prior to their closure for conversion to Metro
K74 held the honour of running the last revenue K set service on the Carlingford line prior to closure in 2020.
Became the "Tekno Train" for Vivid Sydney 2024
Ran the last revenue service through Sydenham platforms 1&2 prior to their closure for conversion to Metro
Inside of doors are grey instead of white.
M3 was the first M set to enter service.
Ran the last revenue service on the Carlingford Line before its closure in 2020.
Seen in the Peter Rabbit (2018) film.
First T set to enter service.
Ex T84. Ran with T74 for the last service on the Epping-Chatswood Rail Link (ECRL) before conversion to Metro.
Second T set to receive Tangara Technology Upgrade
Inactive for some unknown reason. First T set to receive 2010 interior refurbishment.
First T set to receive M set style doors
Ex T132/G32. Last G set built.
Ex G4. First G set to be converted.
Ex G6. First set to receive Tangara Technology Upgrade.
Ex G21. First to receive 2010 interior refurbishment.
Ex G28. Inactive due to TTU upgrades.
Ex G29. Used for ATP testing in 2019.
Ex G30. Occasionally used for ATP testing.
